Been a while since I did a Writer's Talk, so let'sdo it. Todays topic, difficulties of current events inspiration.

When you decide write a fictional story that stats in current time and later spins off into fiction, its good to add some current happenings to flush the current time-line out. Unfortunately if you are using major events that are still ongoing, your story can cometo a screechinghalt if that event goes from relatively clean cut, to uncontrollably insane.

An example of that would be if you wanted to use Donald Trumps Impeachment in the story, because in your view its a stupid thing to do. Only to have the crazy start to pile up.

It went from Impeachment, to Ukraine, to the Wuhan Flue (CCP Flue), to now Riots and burning cities.

You could come to a stand still in your writing it you do want to use crazy things before spinning into fiction. If you have time to wait, great, if not, cut it off early and continue the tale.
